OL,3,CTrapped researchers in Antarctica call
OL,4,Cfor help after 'assault' of colleague
OL,6,FA message from one of the researchers
OL,7,Fshared with South Africa's Sunday
OL,8,FTimes said they were "deeply
OL,9,Fconcerned" about their own safety due
OL,10,Fto a colleagues behaviour.
OL,12,FIt said: "Regrettably, (his) behaviour
OL,13,Fhas escalated to a point that is
OL,14,Fdeeply disturbing. Specifically, he
OL,15,Fphysically assaulted (name withheld),
OL,16,Fwhich is a grave violation of personal
OL,17,Fsafety and workplace norms."
