OL,3,CTrapped researchers in Antarctica call
OL,4,Cfor help after 'assault' of colleague
OL,6,FSouth Africa's Ministry of
OL,7,FEnvironment, which oversees the
OL,8,Fresearch missions, said in a statement
OL,9,FMonday night that the alleged assault
OL,10,Fon the base leader was reported on
OL,11,FFeb. 27, and officials and counselors
OL,12,Fintervened remotely "to mediate and
OL,13,Frestore relationships at the base."
OL,15,F"The alleged perpetrator has willingly
OL,16,Fparticipated in further psychological
OL,17,Fevaluation, has shown remorse and is
OL,18,Fwillingly cooperative," the ministry
OL,19,Fadded.
