OL,3,CTrapped researchers in Antarctica call
OL,4,Cfor help after 'assault' of colleague
OL,6,FThey went on to say the perpetrator
OL,7,Fhad written a formal apology to the
OL,8,Fvictim of the alleged assault. No one
OL,9,Fwas identified and authorities say
OL,10,Fthere are currently no plans to
OL,11,Fevacuate anyone from Sanae IV.
OL,13,FSouth African Environment Minister
OL,14,FDion George appeared to confirm the
OL,15,Fincident, with The Times reporting he
OL,16,Fsaid: "There was a verbal altercation
OL,17,Fbetween the team leader and this
OL,18,Fperson. Then it escalated and then
OL,19,Fthat person did physically assault the
OL,20,Fleader.
